terms.title: Account books
terms.scope_note: Books in which financial accounts are kept.  See also: Housebooks

terms.title: Accounts
terms.scope_note: Documents in which monies or goods received and paid or given out are recorded in order to permit periodic totaling.

terms.title: Address books
terms.scope_note: Books listing names with residences, usually in alphabetical order.  Terms: address books; address book; book, address; books, address.

terms.title: Appointment books
terms.scope_note: Books for recording engagements; usually containing calendars.

terms.title: Architectural drawings (visual works)
terms.scope_note: Drawings of architecture and drawings for architectural projects, whether the project was executed or not. The term may also refer to any image in a two-dimensional medium that serves this same purpose, including prints and computer images.

terms.title: Artifacts (object genre)
terms.scope_note: Objects made, modified, or used by humans.

terms.title: Awards
terms.scope_note: Honors conferred or bestowed, usually including a document or token indicating or symbolizing the award, or remuneration.  Terms: awards; award.

terms.title: Bills (legislative records)
terms.scope_note: Drafts of proposed laws introduced in a legislative body.

terms.title: Blueprints (reprographic copies)
terms.scope_note: Use for reproductive prints of architectural and other technical drawings having white images on blue backgrounds, produced by the blueprint process. For blue images on white backgrounds, use "blueline prints." For blue-toned photographs produced by the blueprint process, use "cyanotypes."

terms.title: Bookplates
terms.scope_note: Labels, usually printed or engraved, frequently with a distinctive design, pasted or tipped into books to mark their ownership or presentation, and sometimes to indicate their location in a library. They are usually attached to the inside of the upper cover.

terms.title: Briefs (legal documents)
terms.scope_note: Concise statements of the arguments of a party to a case in dispute, submitted to the court or other body hearing the case.

terms.title: Brochures
terms.scope_note: Small printed works describing the features or amenities of a place, an organization, or other concern, generally intended as advertisement.

terms.title: Business cards
terms.scope_note: Small cards produced since the 19th century bearing the name and address of a business concern and one of its representatives, and intended more for information than advertisement. For small printed sheets or cards bearing tradesmen's advertisements from the 17th through the 19th century, use "trade cards." For cards made later and distributed for advertisement, use "advertising cards."  Terms: show cards, trade cards

terms.title: Bylaws (administrative records)
terms.scope_note: Laws, ordinances, or regulations made by a public or private corporation, association, or unincorporated society for the regulation of its own local or internal affairs, for its dealings with others, or for the government.

terms.title: Cashbooks
terms.scope_note: Books of original entry in which a record is kept of all cash receipts, disbursements, or both.

terms.title: Certificates
terms.scope_note: Documents giving authoritative recognition of a fact, qualification, or promise.  See also: baptismal C; birth C; C of deposit; C of incorporation; C of occupancy; C of origin; death C; copyright C; gift C; marriage C; stock C, others.

terms.title: Clippings (information artifacts)
terms.scope_note: Illustrations, pages, articles, or columns of text removed from books, newspapers, journals, or other printed sources and kept for their informational content.  Terms: newspaper clippings; press clippings; press cuttings

terms.title: Commonplace books
terms.scope_note: Books in which noteworthy literary passages, cogent quotations, poems, comments, recipes, prescriptions, and other miscellaneous document types are written

terms.title: Contracts
terms.scope_note: Documents, enforceable by law, embodying agreements between two or more competent parties to do or not to do something, and specifying the terms and conditions of the agreement

terms.title: Daybooks
terms.scope_note: Volumes used in bookkeeping containing daily records of receipts and expenditures in the order of their occurrence.

terms.title: Deeds
terms.scope_note: Documents, usually executed under seal, containing a conveyance, especially of real estate.

terms.title: Diaries
terms.scope_note: Refers to books containing the daily, personal accounts of the writer's own experiences, attitudes, and observations.

terms.title: Diplomas
terms.scope_note: Formal documents conferring some honor, degree, or privilege, especially those bearing record of graduation from or a degree conferred by an educational institution.

terms.title: Drawings
terms.scope_note: Visual works produced by drawing, which is the application of lines on a surface, often paper, by using a pencil, pen, chalk, or some other tracing instrument.

terms.title: Engravings
terms.scope_note: Use specifically for prints obtained from an engraved printing surface. Historically, has sometimes been used loosely to refer to all prints. Also in TGM

terms.title: Ephemera (general object genre)
terms.scope_note: Items created, manufactured, or used for a specific, limited use; typically intended to be used for a short period and discarded thereafter, although ephemera is often actually collected. Use for Printed ephemera. (Examples could be broadsides, posters, leaflets, pamphlets, programs, postcards, tradecards, labels, tickets, handbills, sale notices, and valentines.)

terms.title: Field notes
terms.scope_note: Notes, often in books, kept by researchers or surveying parties while on site.

terms.title: Fliers (printed matter)
terms.scope_note: Printed pieces such as notices or advertisements intended for distribution by hand or by mail. For those intended for posting, use "posters."

terms.title: Glass plate negatives
terms.scope_note: Sheets of glass coated with light-sensitive emulsion that have been exposed and developed, and that are intended as matrices for the creation of positive photographic prints on another support.

terms.title: Handbills
terms.scope_note: Small printed sheets usually containing a notice or advertisement intended for distribution by hand and often doubling as posters.  For larger pieces, intended especially for posting, use "posters." In rbgenr as: Broadsides.

terms.title: Housebooks
terms.scope_note: Documents in which are recorded household expenditures such as for food, utilities, and domestic help, maintained in a journal or other book; also includes classed or chronological files of the bills and receipts for household goods and services.

terms.title: Interviews
terms.scope_note: Statements, transcripts, or recordings of conversations in which one person obtains information from another such as for research purposes, publication, or broadcast.

terms.title: Invitations
terms.scope_note: Engraved, printed, or written expressions soliciting or requesting a person's company at a certain event at a given time and place.

terms.title: Invoices
terms.scope_note: Documents showing items supplied, together with the prices charged for each; also, itemized bills or accounts.

terms.title: Journals (accounts)
terms.scope_note: Use for books containing accounts of an individual's or organization's occurrences or transactions, including records of financial transactions. Use "diaries" when referring to personal accounts of the writer's experiences, attitudes, or observations.

terms.title: Juvenilia
terms.scope_note: Literary or artistic works produced by persons in their childhood or youth; usually used to set those works apart from later, mature works.

terms.title: Land surveys
terms.scope_note: Use for documents, often maps, which record the measuring and marking of land.

terms.title: Lantern slides
terms.scope_note: Transparent positive images made or mounted on glass for projection, usually but not necessarily photographic, measuring 3 1/4 to 3 1/2 by 4 inches.

terms.title: Ledgers (account books)
terms.scope_note: Volumes of final entry in accounting in which are entered debits, credits, and all other money transactions under each individual account or heading.

terms.title: Legal documents
terms.scope_note: Use instead of Legal records.

terms.title: Letterpress copybooks
terms.scope_note: Books containing letterpress copies.

terms.title: Maps (documents)
terms.scope_note: Refers to graphic or photogrammetric representations of the Earth's surface or a part of it, including physical features and political boundaries, where each point corresponds to a geographical or celestial position according to a definite scale or projection. The term may also refer to similar depictions of other planets, suns, other heavenly bodies, or areas of the heavens. Maps are typically depicted on a flat medium, such as on paper, a wall, or a computer screen.

terms.title: Memoirs
terms.scope_note: Narratives or histories autobiographical in nature or stressing the author's personal experience of the events.

terms.title: Military commissions
terms.scope_note: Warrants conferring authority to raise and command a body of troops; certificates conferring military or naval rank and authority on officers of certain rank.

terms.title: Motion pictures (visual works)
terms.scope_note: Use for works presented in the form of a series of pictures carried on photographic film or video tape, presented to the eye in such rapid succession as to give the illusion of natural movement.

terms.title: Muster rolls
terms.scope_note: Lists of troops actually present, made on the day of muster or review of troops in order to take account of their condition; used as the paymaster's voucher for the pay he issued.

terms.title: Oral Histories (document genres)
terms.scope_note: Use for those works that record interviews conducted to preserve the recollections of persons whose experience or memories are representative or are of special historical or social significance.

terms.title: Orderly books
terms.scope_note: Books kept at the headquarters of a military unit, such as a regiment or company, in which orders received from higher authorities are recorded.

terms.title: Paintings (visual works)
terms.scope_note: Unique works in which images are formed primarily by the direct application of pigments suspended in oil, water, egg yolk, molten wax, or other liquid, arranged in masses of color, onto a generally two-dimensional surface.

terms.title: Pamphlets
terms.scope_note: Independent publications consisting of a few leaves of printed matter folded or fastened together but not bound, often with no cover or a paper cover.  For smaller printed works, of one sheet folded and not stitched or bound, use "leaflets."

terms.title: Photograph albums
terms.scope_note: Albums made up of mounted photographs, with or without identifying information.

terms.title: Posters
terms.scope_note: Notices usually decorative or pictorial, intended to be posted to advertise, promote, or publicize an activity, cause, product, or service; also, decorative, mass-produced prints intended for hanging. For small printed notices or advertisements intended for distribution by hand, use "handbills."

terms.title: Prints (visual works)
terms.scope_note: Pictorial works produced by transferring images by means of a matrix such as a plate, block, or screen, using any of various printing processes.

terms.title: Prompt books
terms.scope_note: Copies of plays used by a prompter, showing action of the play, cues, movements of actors, properties, costume, and scene and light plots.

terms.title: School yearbooks
terms.scope_note: Annual publications of schools that provide information and often photographs relating to activities and the students at the school during the previous year.

terms.title: Scrapbooks
terms.scope_note: Blank books or albums designed so that a variety of items may be affixed to the pages, including photographs, clippings and other memorabilia.

terms.title: Scripts (documents)
terms.scope_note: Written texts of stage plays, screenplays, and radio or television broadcasts.

terms.title: Sermons
terms.scope_note: Religious discourses delivered as part of a church service, usually delivered from a pulpit, based upon a text of scripture, and with the purpose of giving religious instruction or exhortation.

terms.title: Sheet music
terms.scope_note: Music printed on unbound sheets of paper.

terms.title: Shipping records
terms.scope_note: Records of goods or cargo shipped.

terms.title: Ships’ logs
terms.scope_note: Daily records of the progress of a ship at sea, with notes on the weather and important incidents of the voyage.

terms.title: Sketchbooks
terms.scope_note: Books or pads of blank sheets used or intended for sketching, which are informal and rough drawings.

terms.title: Sketches
terms.scope_note: Use for rough or summary art works; less finished than studies. Though sketches are often in the drawing medium, the term "drawings" in general implies more finished works than does "sketches."

terms.title: Slides (photographs)
terms.scope_note: Positive transparencies in mounts suitable for projection, usually 35mm film in a mount of 2 by 2 inches.   OTHER CHOICES: lantern slides

terms.title: Trade cards (advertising)
terms.scope_note: Small printed sheets, and later cards, bearing tradesmen's advertisements, often including an engraved illustration; produced from the 17th through the 19th century. For cards made later, bearing the name and address of a business concern and the name of its representative, and intended more for information than for advertising, use "business cards." For cards made later and distributed for advertisement, use "advertising cards."

terms.title: Visiting cards
terms.scope_note: Small cards bearing the name, and sometimes the address of a person or married couple for presentation, as when formally calling or visiting.

terms.title: Visitors’ books
terms.scope_note: Books, usually of printed forms, in which visitors may write their names and addresses, and sometimes comments.

terms.title: Military records
terms.scope_note: Official documents detailing an individual’s service and conduct while in military service, including certificates of discharge.
